          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          <strong>About:</strong> Following the death of her husband, Petr Kellner, Renata became one of Europe’s wealthiest women as the head of the PPF Group. The conglomerate spans telecom, banking, and media, wielding immense influence in Central and Eastern Europe. She has stepped into leadership roles to ensure PPF’s growth. Her low public profile contrasts with her massive economic sway.</p>
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">
          <strong>Need to Know:</strong> Renata faced a high-stakes battle to manage PPF’s sprawling assets after her husband's sudden helicopter crash. She fiercely protects her family’s privacy, but her strategic decisions in finance are making waves. Her wealth often attracts speculation, with the media calling her Europe’s “hidden financial queen.”​</p>
          
